main event: Radar contact established with a UFO, observed on radar approaching at high speeds.
interesting points: The radar contact was made at 2352Z with two targets closing at 1,500 knots., The observation lasted 132 minutes with only radar data available., A naval message described the UFO as a large, round, white object., The object was estimated to be at an elevation of 335 feet and traveling from east to west., No visual sighting was made; only radar data was used for assessment.
